         <abstract>
            <p>
               Let $f(x)$ be a polynomial over a finite field $F$. An algorithm for determining the degrees of the factors of $f(x)$ is presented. As in the Berlekamp algorithm (1968) for determining the factors of $f(x)$, the Frobenius endomorphism on $F\lbrack x \rbrack/(f(x))$ plays a central role. Little-known theorems of Schwarz (1956) and Ces√†ro (1888) provide the basis for the algorithm we present. New and stream-lined proofs of both theorems are provided. 
            </p>
          </abstract>
